          MODULE=kavi2svcd
         VERSION=0.8.5
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.gz
   SOURCE_URL[0]=$SFORGE_URL/$MODULE/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha1:79aab6e18d65a436bee4d16fbf8c7667b60d3ae4
        WEB_SITE=http://www.cornelinux.de/web/linux/kavi2svcd/index-english.html
         ENTERED=20050618
         UPDATED=20050618
           SHORT="a GUI method to generate an mpeg-file from an avi-file"

cat << EOF
kavi2svcd is a grahphical user interface that generates an mpeg-file from an avi-file
using transcode and mplex, from the mpeg-file it generates an image for a Video-CD 
using vcdimager and finally it burns the CD with cdrdao. 

Features
Generating of the m1v/m2v und mpa-files
Multiplexing the mpegfile
Generating the cue/bin-files
Burning the CDs
Saving usual configuration data (VCD-type, CD-Size, burning speed, burning device?)
The command lines are generated and can be edited before executing.
EOF
